    <item>
      <title>Deactivate automatic capitalization</title>
      <link>https://lanceleonard.com/tips/web/html/auto-capitalization/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lanceleonard.com/tips/web/html/auto-capitalization/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Most browser automatically capitalize text input elements, which is convenient most of the time.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This can create problems when case matters, such as password fields, recovery codes, or other values.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use the &lt;code&gt;autocapitalize&lt;/code&gt; attribute to deactivate (or &lt;em&gt;disable&lt;/em&gt;) automatic capitalization for a specific field.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s an example:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-html&#34; data-lang=&#34;html&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;label&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;example&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Enter a lowercase value:&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;label&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;input&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;text&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;example&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;example&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;autocapitalize&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;false&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&#34;https://caniuse.com/?search=autocomplete&#34;&gt;Can I Use?&lt;/a&gt;, the default behavior varies according to the browser and the device.  When creating web apps for use on desktop and mobile devices, it&amp;rsquo;s best to test real world value on a variety devices.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Hide details until needed</title>
      <link>https://lanceleonard.com/tips/web/html/details-element/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lanceleonard.com/tips/web/html/details-element/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The &amp;lt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/details&#34;&gt;details&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt; element (also known as the &lt;em&gt;disclosure element&lt;/em&gt;) hides content until a user chooses to view it.  You can use this element to reduce the visual impact of large content blocks, such as extended source code, detailed configuration files, videos, and so on.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;By default, &amp;lt;details&amp;gt; hides content until the user chooses to view it.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &amp;lt;details&amp;gt; element is a core HTML element supported by many &lt;a href=&#34;https://caniuse.com/?search=details&#34;&gt;modern browsers&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;example&#34;&gt;Example&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s an example of the &amp;lt;details&amp;gt; element:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
